WITH consumption_data AS (
    SELECT t.column_4 AS customer_id, SUM(t.column_8) AS total_consumption_eur
    FROM transactions_1k t
    JOIN yearmonth y ON t.column_1 = y.column_1::date
    WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM t.column_1) IN (2012, 2013)
    GROUP BY t.column_4, EXTRACT(YEAR FROM t.column_1)
),
segment_data AS (
    SELECT c.column_0 AS customer_id, c.column_1 AS segment
    FROM customers c
)
SELECT s.segment,
       ((c2.total_consumption_eur - c1.total_consumption_eur) / c1.total_consumption_eur::real * 100) AS percentage_increase
FROM consumption_data c1
JOIN consumption_data c2 ON c1.customer_id = c2.customer_id AND c1.customer_id IS NOT DISTINCT FROM c2.customer_id AND EXTRACT(YEAR FROM c1.column_1) < EXTRACT(YEAR FROM c2.column_1)
JOIN segment_data s ON c1.customer_id = s.customer_id
WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM c1.column_1) = 2012 AND EXTRACT(YEAR FROM c2.column_1) = 2013
GROUP BY s.segment, ((c2.total_consumption_eur - c1.total_consumption_eur) / c1.total_consumption_eur::real * 100)
ORDER BY percentage_increase DESC
LIMIT 1

UNION ALL

       ((c2.total_consumption_eur - c1.total_consumption_eur) / c1.total_consumption_eur::real * 100) AS percentage_increase

JOIN segment_data s ON c1.customer_id = s.customer_id
